Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a splash of oil. Remove the skin from the @Tuscan Pork Sausage{500} by slitting along its length. Remove the sausage meat (discard the skin) and break into 2cm chunks. Pop these into the frying pan and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}. You want them to brown nice and gently. Turn every now and then to make sure they don't burn.

Wash your hands and then get on with the rest of your prep. Cut the @Echalion Shallot{2} in half through the root, peel and slice into thin half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @Red Pepper{2} and slice as thinly as you can. Once your sausage meat is cooked remove to a #plate{}, then add your pepper and shallot to the pan. Cook for another ~{5-7%minutes} or until soft.

Pour the @Tomato Passata{2} into a #small bowl{}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{pinch}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Pick the @Basil{1} leaves and shred them finely. Add your garlic and basil to your tomato passata. Taste and add more salt and black pepper if necessary. This is your tomato sauce.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Place a @Super Soft Tortillas with Whole Wheat{8} on a #chopping board{}. Smear a spoonful of your tomato sauce across your tortilla. Leave a 1cm border free of sauce. Put some @Baby Spinach{1} leaves in the centre, and then top with a few pieces of sausage, red pepper and shallot. Roll to enclose the filling and then pop into a lightly greased #baking dish{} with the join side down.

Repeat until you have two filled tortillas per person. Spoon your remaining tomato sauce on top of your rolled tortillas and then sprinkle over the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40}.

Pop your baking dish on the top shelf of your oven for ~{12-15%minutes} or until your cheese is golden and bubbling. Have a quick clear up and get the washing up done whilst your tortillas bake.

Mix the @Balsamic Vinegar{1} with the @Olive Oil{2} and drizzle it over the @Wild Rocket{1}. Serve your baked tortillas on a bed of rocket. Enjoy!